  <key id="d0" for="node" attr.name="entity_type" attr.type="string" />
  <graph edgedefault="undirected">
    <node id="&quot;MARKET-TOWN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The market-town is depicted as a nostalgic location from Scrooge's past, filled with joyful memories and interactions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ship symbolizes the connection among sailors who share thoughts of Christmas despite being far from home."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GIRL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Girl, unnamed, represents the plight of the poor and marginalized, emphasizing the impact of societal indifference towards the vulnerable."&lt;SEP&gt;"The girl is a character who assists Scrooge at his nephew's house, representing the hospitality and warmth of the Christmas spirit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE AND MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge and Marley is the business partnership representing the mercantile values and miserly operations of Scrooge and his deceased partner, Marley."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WINE-MERCHANT'S CELLAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Wine-Merchant's Cellar is part of Scrooge's home, inferring it may have historical significance in relation to wealth and past dealings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SURREAL EVENING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Surreal Evening embodies the strangeness of the experiences Scrooge faces as he confronts Marley's Ghost."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SOOTHING WIND OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Soothing Wind of Change indicates the calming presence of upheaval pushing Scrooge toward growth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CELESTIAL DANCE OF SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Celestial Dance of Spirits signifies the harmony of guidance and support from the spirits on Scrooge's journey."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SNOW&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Snow symbolizes the winter setting and evokes memories for Scrooge, enhancing the atmosphere of reflection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHILDREN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Children are part of the Old Man's family, enjoying the holiday season and participating in the singing of Christmas songs."&lt;SEP&gt;"The children shown by the Spirit represent the worst outcomes of poverty and societal failure, calling attention to urgent social issues."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GENTLEMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Gentleman represents the voice of social concern, advocating for the poor and seeking assistance during the festive season."&lt;SEP&gt;"The gentleman is an old character who engages with Scrooge, highlighting themes of kindness and recognition during the Christmas season."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD SCRATCH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Scratch refers to the devil or mischief, symbolizing temptation and the darker aspects of human nature, mentioned humorously in the conversation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FIREPLACE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Fireplace is an old structure in Scrooge's dwelling that symbolizes warmth and comfort, contrasting with Scrooge's cold nature."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FOOTSTEPS OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Footsteps of Change represent the growing awareness in Scrooge that transformation is possible."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE REBIRTH OF MOTIVATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Rebirth of Motivation embodies the renewed drive that Scrooge experiences as he embraces transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PULSE OF GENEROSITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Pulse of Generosity highlights the revitalization of the joyful spirit within Scrooge as he embraces giving."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirit is an ethereal figure encountered by Scrooge that represents a connection to his past, guiding him through memories."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents a ghostly figure guiding Scrooge, embodying themes of morality and the consequences of one's actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents a supernatural entity that guides Scrooge through a reflective journey, revealing societal issues and personal shortcomings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GROG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Grog is a type of drink shared by the two men at the lighthouse, reflecting camaraderie and warmth during their isolated Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;STREET&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The street serves as a setting for Scrooge's joyful journey as he interacts with various townsfolk during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BED-CURTAINS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bed-curtains are mentioned humorously in relation to a conversation, symbolizing the mundane aspects of life juxtaposed with themes of death and mourning."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CASK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Casks in the wine-merchant's cellar signify storage of wealth and suggest a past filled with indulgence and commerce."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COUNTDOWN TO REDEMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Countdown to Redemption underscores the urgency for Scrooge to embrace change before time runs out."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CANDLE OF HOPE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Candle of Hope signifies the light that guides Scrooge toward a new path and understanding of compassion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE AURORA OF HOPE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Aurora of Hope represents the dawn of new experiences and feelings for Scrooge as he transforms."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The weather is described as cold and snowy, setting the mood for reflection and nostalgia during Scrooge's journey with the Spirit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TWO MEN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Two Men at the lighthouse share a moment of celebration and camaraderie while braving the harsh sea conditions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE YOUNG HOUSEKEEPERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The young housekeepers represent a generational connection to traditional Christmas celebrations, concerned with the proper way to set a festive table."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CRATCHIT FAMILY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Cratchit Family is a group of individuals that includes Bob, Mrs. Cratchit, Tiny Tim, and the Cratchit children, depicting a loving but struggling family coming together for Christmas dinner."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Cratchit Family represents a close-knit family unit that displays resilience and joy, despite their financial struggles."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DUTCH MERCHANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dutch Merchant represents historical influence in the construction and design of Scrooge's fireplace."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAST CHANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Last Chance encapsulates the critical moment when Scrooge must decide to change before it's too late."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE AWAKENING OF SELF-AWARENESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Awakening of Self-Awareness highlights the realization Scrooge has about his true needs and desires."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GENTLE GUIDANCE OF THE SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Gentle Guidance of the Spirit captures how the spirits offer support during Scrooge's path toward redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOYS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The boys are characters seen in Scrooge's memories who embody the joyful spirit of childhood and Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SETTING SUN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Setting Sun symbolizes the transition from day to night, providing a backdrop for the desolate yet beautiful landscape."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DINING-ROOM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The dining-room is the setting for familial gatherings, representing warmth and togetherness during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS DINNER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Christmas Dinner is the festive meal prepared by Mrs. Cratchit for her family, filled with joy and celebration despite their modest means, highlighting themes of family and gratitude."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas Dinner symbolizes the gathering and celebration of the Cratchit family, showcasing warmth and togetherness during the holiday season."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GRATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Grate is part of the fireplace where the fire burns, symbolizing warmth and the small comfort Scrooge allows himself."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE VISIT OF MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Visit of Marley sets the stage for Scrooge's confrontation with his own failings and the possibility of change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE JOURNEY OF THE HEART&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Journey of the Heart encapsulates Scrooge's emotional experiences as he connects with others and himself."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Journey of the Heart symbolizes the emotional exploration that allows Scrooge to connect genuinely with others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE RADIANCE OF CONNECTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Radiance of Connection highlights the importance of relationships as Scrooge embraces positive change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FARMERS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The farmers are depicted in Scrooge's recollections of the market-town, contributing to the lively atmosphere of his youthful memories."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MOOR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Moor is depicted as a bleak landscape where miners live, highlighting themes of hardship and the contrast with festive moments."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CAB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The cab represents a means of transportation that facilitates Scrooge's participation in Christmas festivities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS HOLLOY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Christmas Holly is a decorative element used to adorn the pudding, symbolizing festivity and traditional Christmas celebrations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE NIGHTCAP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Nightcap is an article of clothing worn by Scrooge, indicating his readiness to relax and his adherence to routine."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GRIEF OF CHOICES UNMADE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Grief of Choices Unmade symbolizes the sorrow Scrooge feels for opportunities he has not taken."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE UNRAVELING THREADS OF LIFE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Unraveling Threads of Life symbolize the interconnected nature of choices that shape our destinies."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TAPESTRY OF LEGACY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Tapestry of Legacy encapsulates how Scrooge’s choices weave into the fabric of his identity and impact."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WINTER DAY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The winter day serves as a backdrop for Scrooge's journey, emphasizing themes of coldness that contrast with the warmth of memories."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHRISTMAS SONG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Christmas Song sung by the Old Man and his family emphasizes the spirit of joy, celebration, and togetherness during the holiday."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE STREETS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The streets signify communal engagement during Christmas as Scrooge experiences the festive atmosphere."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CRATCHIT CHILDREN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Cratchit children are the offspring of Bob and Mrs. Cratchit, contributing to the lively atmosphere during Christmas dinner with their excitement and cherubic innocence."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DRESSING-GOWN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dressing-Gown is a garment that reflects Scrooge's nighttime comfort and solitude, reinforcing his character's traits."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE REPENTANCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Repentance signifies Scrooge's yearning for forgiveness and a chance to rectify past wrongs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SYMPHONY OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Symphony of Change illustrates the harmonious transitions available to Scrooge as he evolves."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Symphony of Change resonates with the harmony of transformation that Scrooge embarks upon in his journey."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CRUCIBLE OF EXPERIENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Crucible of Experience represents the challenges and lessons that shape Scrooge’s growth over time."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GATE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The gate symbolizes entry points into different phases of Scrooge's life, reflecting on paths taken and memories made."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ABYSS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Abyss represents the unknown and danger, representing Scrooge's fears and the potential consequences of his past actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PEOPLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The people encountered by Scrooge during his walk embody the joy and camaraderie of the Christmas spirit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE HEARTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Hearth is the central part of the Cratchit home, where the family gathers, symbolizing warmth, comfort, and togetherness."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CANDLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Candle signifies Scrooge's source of light in the dark, paralleling the theme of enlightenment versus ignorance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE HOPE OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Hope of Change embodies the potential for a new beginning and the uplifting possibility of redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPECTRUM OF EMOTIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spectrum of Emotions represents the various feelings Scrooge experiences throughout his metamorphosis."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SERPENTINE PATH TOWARD GROWTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Serpentine Path toward Growth highlights the non-linear journey of transformation for Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JACOB MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner who appears as a ghost, urging Scrooge to change his ways."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner whose ghost appears to warn Scrooge about the consequences of his actions and the importance of change."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, known for his ghostly visit that serves as a catalyst for Scrooge's transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is a deceased character who predicts the consequences of Scrooge's actions, indicating the need for change in his life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is a spirit associated with Scrooge's past, urging him to change his ways and recognize the value of Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is presented as a ghostly figure, who was once Scrooge's business partner and now appears as a specter."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is the ghost of Scrooge's former business partner, who warns Scrooge about the consequences of his life choices and the nature of regret."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARTHA CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Martha Cratchit is Bob's daughter who arrives home late and is greeted with affection by her family, showcasing familial love and warmth."&lt;SEP&gt;"Martha Cratchit is another daughter in the Cratchit family, who works as an apprentice and expresses aspirations for rest and leisure during the holiday."&lt;SEP&gt;"Martha Cratchit is another daughter of Bob Cratchit, serving as a representation of family togetherness."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
