    <node id="&quot;BLIND MAN'S-BUFF&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Blind man's-buff is a children's game that Bob Cratchit's family plays, illustrating the innocence and joy present in their holiday celebrations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ALMONDS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Almonds are a common ingredient in holiday recipes and gifts, symbolizing sweetness and prosperity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERCY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mercy represents the compassion and kindness embodied by Scrooge after his transformation, leading to his desire to help others."&lt;SEP&gt;"The plea for mercy by Scrooge indicates his fear and desperation in the face of the spectral visitation, representing a moment of vulnerability."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CLOAK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Cloak is part of Scrooge's nighttime attire, reinforcing his insulated and introverted character."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE REFLECTION IN THE PAST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Reflection in the Past signifies the crucial moments that form the turning points in Scrooge's life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EMBERS OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Embers of Change represent the small beginnings of transformation that spark a renewed life for Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FUSION OF HEART AND MIND&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Fusion of Heart and Mind highlights the alignment of Scrooge's emotions with his newfound ethical beliefs."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MATERIAL POSSESSIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The material possessions represented by Marley's chain signify the weight of greed and the burdens carried into the afterlife."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WORKHOUSES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Workhouses represent the societal structures that enable poverty and the neglect of the needy."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD JOE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Joe is a character who displays a mix of cynicism and humor as he discusses the deceased man's belongings, indicating a lack of empathy for the dead."&lt;SEP&gt;"Old Joe is an elderly character who runs a shop where various wares are dealt in. He humorously interacts with three individuals who come to meet him, showcasing his calm demeanor despite their dubious activities."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CINNAMON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
