      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DISCOVERY OF COMPASSION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Discovery of Compassion signifies Scrooge's journey to realizing the importance of caring for others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CONNECTION OF ELSEWHERE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Connection of Elsewhere reflects the broader implications of Scrooge's journey on his community and beyond."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIGS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Figs are a seasonal fruit that may find their way into Christmas desserts and celebrations, symbolizing abundance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BOB CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, depicted as a hardworking individual with a modest income who tries to provide for his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, representing the struggles of the working class and the value of family in A Christmas Carol."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, who, despite Scrooge's ill-tempered nature, cherishes the Christmas spirit and looks forward to holiday celebrations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a father who shows deep emotional connection to his family, particularly to his son, Tiny Tim, and displays resilience despite hardships."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a loving father figure who expresses happiness and reflects on the teachings of Tiny Tim."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a supportive character in the story, who represents the working-class struggle and embodies a spirit of warmth and kindness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is an employee of Scrooge who is often late to work; he struggles to support his family and experiences a significant change in his circumstances after Scrooge's transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is an employee of Scrooge, symbolizing kindness and the struggles of the working class, and becomes a recipient of Scrooge's generosity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is depicted as a father figure, associated with a humble household and significant emotional resilience in the face of hardship."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father of Tiny Tim and the head of the Cratchit family, characterized by his warmth and dedication to his family's well-being, as well as his role in the Christmas dinner celebration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father of the Cratchit family, portrayed as caring and devoted, anxious about his children's well-being, especially Tiny Tim."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PRISONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Prisons symbolize the consequences of societal failure to address the underlying issues of poverty and ignorance."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MRS. DILBER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mrs. Dilber is a laundress employed by Scrooge and presents a view of Scrooge’s relationship with the working class."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Dilber is a laundress who participates in a morally questionable gathering in Old Joe's shop, showcasing a pragmatic attitude and camaraderie with the other characters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
