    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TINY TIM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's son, a symbol of innocence and hope, known for his kind spirit despite his physical challenges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a symbol of innocence and hope, remembered with affection by Scrooge and the Cratchit family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a symbolic character in Scrooge's journey, representing innocence and the spirit of Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a young boy and a member of the Cratchit family, known for his frail health and optimistic spirit, often expressing gratitude and love for his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the Cratchit family's ill child, symbolizing innocence and the impact of loss on a family unit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the ill son of Bob Cratchit, representing innocence and the need for compassion in society."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the son of Bob Cratchit, representing innocence and hope, who benefits from Scrooge's newfound generosity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the young son of Bob and Mrs. Cratchit, symbolizing innocence and vulnerability, and is deeply loved by his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is the youngest Cratchit child, known for his disability which he bears with a hopeful and cheerful spirit, inspiring others with his outlook."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim, also known as Tim Cratchit, is a small, disabled boy who symbolizes innocence and the impact of poverty on families during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DARKNESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Darkness conveys the themes of despair and the unknown future that looms over Scrooge and society as a whole."&lt;SEP&gt;"Darkness represents the absence of clarity and knowledge that envelops Scrooge during the narrative, contrasting with the light brought by The Visitor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WOMAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Woman is a bold character with a heavy bundle, who engages in a conversation about morality and the deceased, highlighting a sense of defiance and opportunism."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Woman shares a laugh with Joe, showing a lack of reverence for the deceased and a practical attitude towards material gain from his death."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
