    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOTAL-ABSTINENCE PRINCIPLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Total-Abstinence Principle refers to Scrooge's commitment to a life of moderation and restraint, which he adopts after his transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MRS. CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit's wife, showing the strength of family and the struggles they face in maintaining hope despite hardship."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob's wife, responsible for preparing the family's Christmas dinner, showing pride in her cooking and a sense of nervous anticipation about the meal."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is Bob's wife, working hard to manage their household despite limited resources, contributing to her family's celebrations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is a caring mother figure in the Cratchit family, embodying warmth and love during the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is depicted as a strong-willed character who expresses her feelings about Scrooge and seeks to provide happiness for her family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Mrs. Cratchit is portrayed as a caring mother who takes pride in her family's work and supports her husband, Bob, emotionally during difficult times."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BUNDLE&quot;">
