      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE REFLECTION OF GROWTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Reflection of Growth highlights the changes that Scrooge undergoes as he reconciles with his past and present."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE IDOL OF GOLD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Idol of Gold represents the pursuit of wealth that replaces other aspirations and relationships, symbolizing greed and materialism."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ESSENCE OF CHRISTMAS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The essence of Christmas encapsulates themes of generosity, community, and kindness, as portrayed throughout the text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HEAVY BUNDLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Heavy Bundle is the load carried by The Woman, containing items of questionable origin that she brings into the shop for appraisal."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;YOUNG CRATCHITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Young Cratchits are the other children in the Cratchit family, contributing to the familial warmth and joy despite their circumstances."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE IRON FIREGUARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Iron Fireguard symbolizes protection and safety from the metaphorical fires of life that Scrooge faces."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LESSONS OF LOVE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Lessons of Love signify the importance of connections and kindness that Scrooge must relearn."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EVOLUTION OF SELF&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Evolution of Self captures Scrooge's transformation from a miserly individual to a generous soul."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WISDOM OF THE AGES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Wisdom of the Ages represents the accumulated knowledge and lessons we can learn from our experiences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DICK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dick is one of the 'prentices who feels grateful towards Fezziwig, expressing joyful emotions during the dance at the Domestic Ball."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LITTLE FAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Little Fan is Scrooge's younger sister who brings joy and a sense of homecoming to him, representing childhood innocence and warmth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Marley's Ghost is a supernatural visitor who warns Scrooge about his fate and the coming of three spirits, symbolizing regret and the consequences of one's actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley's Ghost is an unearthly visitor troubling Scrooge, who represents a significant supernatural element in the narrative."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley's Ghost represents the supernatural element, appearing to Scrooge and symbolizing his past actions and choices that weigh on him."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPIRITS OF ALL THREE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirits of all Three signify the Past, Present, and Future, guiding Scrooge towards understanding and redeeming his life choices."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPIRITS WITH CHAINS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirits with Chains are symbolic of the burdens that haunt those who have not lived morally."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BRIDGE OF HOPE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Bridge of Hope serves as a metaphor for the path toward a brighter future Scrooge is encouraged to take."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EMBRACE OF CONNECTIONS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Embrace of Connections signifies Scrooge's journey towards valuing relationships with others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE THRESHOLD OF UNDERSTANDING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Threshold of Understanding signifies the pivotal moments of realization that guide personal growth."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BELLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Belle is Scrooge's former lover, who is mentioned in his recollections, embodying what he lost due to his choices."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TWO APPRENTICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Two Apprentices are characters who appreciate Fezziwig's kindness and the joyful atmosphere of the Domestic Ball."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MASTER SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Master Scrooge refers to the younger version of Scrooge, who is shown in a vulnerable state and interacts with his sister and schoolmaster."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THREE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Three Spirits represent Scrooge's impending encounters meant to guide him towards redemption and understanding of his life choices."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SHADOWS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Shadows signify the unseen influences and foreboding nature of Scrooge's past and future actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GIFTS OF THE PRESENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Gifts of the Present emphasize the importance of cherishing now and the relationships in Scrooge's life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LEGACY OF KINDNESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Legacy of Kindness reflects the impact of Scrooge's newly embraced values on future generations."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE INTERPLAY OF SHADOWS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Interplay of Shadows underscores the contrasts between hope and despair as Scrooge navigates his fears."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirit appears to guide Scrooge on his journey, revealing truths about Christmas and human connection."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is a supernatural entity representing the Ghost of Christmas Present that brings lessons of joy and kindness to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents a supernatural figure associated with generosity and goodwill, embodying the essence of Christmas and influencing Scrooge's perception."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents the Ghost of Christmas Past, guiding Scrooge through his memories and reflections."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents the essence of a person's morality and soul which one must confront, as portrayed by the Ghost's message to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit represents the ghostly figures that visit Scrooge, particularly in the context of his transformation and reflection on life choices."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DICK WILKINS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Dick Wilkins is Scrooge's fellow apprentice, associated with companionship and memories from Scrooge's youth."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dick Wilkins is a former apprentice of Scrooge who is fondly remembered by him, indicating a close relationship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;INVISIBLE WORLD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Invisible World refers to the supernatural realm that is revealed to Scrooge, highlighting themes of fate, regret, and the afterlife."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PORTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Porter is a character who is attacked and stripped of his parcels, highlighting the chaos and irrepressible affection among the children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OLD SHOES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Old Shoes represent the remnants of Scrooge's past life, reinforcing the theme of memory and history."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DESCENT INTO DESPAIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Descent into Despair illustrates Scrooge's struggles with loneliness and disconnection from the world around him."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DANCE OF REDEMPTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dance of Redemption symbolizes the active process of embracing change and fostering connections."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE EMBRACE OF JOY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Embrace of Joy captures the essence of happiness that Scrooge begins to reclaim in his life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;POVERTY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Poverty is presented as a significant hardship that contrasts with Scrooge's desire for wealth, influencing his character and choices."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WAREHOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Warehouse is where young Scrooge was apprenticed, representing his early career and formative experiences."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;PHANTOMS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Phantoms are spirits of the departed who are seen wandering restless, portraying grief and desire to assist the living."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MOTHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mother is a character depicted as being present in the family setting, representing warmth and familial love."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OLD FIRE-GUARD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Old Fire-guard signifies past comforts that no longer hold warmth in Scrooge's life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ASCENDANCE OF LIGHT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ascendance of Light symbolizes the emergence of newfound hope and joy in Scrooge’s life as he transforms."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TAPESTRY OF CHOICES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Tapestry of Choices captures the interlinked decisions that shape Scrooge’s life path."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DIVIDENDS OF KINDNESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dividends of Kindness reflect the rewards and blessings that come from acts of compassion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HAPPINESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Happiness is a state that Scrooge remembers fondly from his past experiences, especially in relation to Fezziwig and the joyous atmosphere created."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SCHOOLMASTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Schoolmaster is a character who teaches at the school Scrooge attended, representing authority and discipline in Scrooge's early life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BELL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Bell is a disused object in Scrooge's home that, when it begins to swing, signals the supernatural events taking place."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Bell represents the passage of time and marks significant moments, including the arrival of the spirits to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Bell, which tolls before the visitation, signifies a marker of time and foreshadows the arrival of The Visitor."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost refers to the supernatural entities that interact with Scrooge, showcasing the thematic elements of redemption and reflection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAYERS OF DUST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Layers of Dust symbolize neglect and the passage of time in Scrooge's home and life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FLAMES OF CHANGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Flames of Change represent the intense feelings and energy surrounding Scrooge's journey toward redemption."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FLOWS OF GENEROSITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Flows of Generosity represent Scrooge's newfound commitment to giving and sharing with others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TRANSFORMATIVE NATURE OF COURAGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Transformative Nature of Courage illustrates how bravery can lead to meaningful change in one's life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAMPLIGHTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Lamplighter is a character who spreads light in the darkness, serving as a symbol of joy and cheer during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FATHER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Father is referenced as Little Fan's parent, indicating a change in his demeanor towards kindness and family."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Father is the husband in the family scene who enjoys the affectionate company of his wife and children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CLOCK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Clock is described as having inaccurate timekeeping which causes confusion for Scrooge, symbolizing his disorientation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Clock symbolizes time's relentless advancement and Scrooge's struggle with understanding its passage, particularly during his transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"The clock represents the passage of time and anticipation within the Cratchit household, underscoring their anxious wait for news."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FIRESIDE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Fireside represents a warm and cozy setting in the home, indicative of familial love and togetherness during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WINTER COLD&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Winter Cold represents the harshness of Scrooge's environment and his emotional state."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MOSAIC OF MEMORIES&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mosaic of Memories captures how past experiences interweave to shape Scrooge’s actions and identity."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BLOSSOMING OF HUMANITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Blossoming of Humanity signifies Scrooge's awakening to the essential nature of human connection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DELIGHT OF FRIENDSHIP&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Delight of Friendship signifies the joy found in building relationships and connecting with others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OLD MAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Old Man sings a Christmas song alongside his family, representing tradition and the joy of the holiday season."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE COACH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Coach is a mode of transportation that Little Fan uses to bring Scrooge home, symbolizing reunion and transition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE AIR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Air is described as filled with phantoms and supernatural elements, illustrating the eerie and haunting atmosphere around Scrooge's encounters."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BROWN-PAPER PARCELS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Brown-paper parcels symbolize the joy and excitement of gift-giving and the festive spirit of Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPIRITS OF CHRISTMAS PAST, PRESENT, AND FUTURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirits of Christmas Past, Present, and Future represent the journey Scrooge undertakes to confront his life choices and their implications."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE FOUNDATION OF THE FUTURE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Foundation of the Future signifies the lessons learned that will support Scrooge's decisions moving forward."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TRANSFORMATION OF THE SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Transformation of the Spirit illustrates the changes that come from embracing love and connection."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LAYERS OF CONNECTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Layers of Connection reflect the complexities and depths of relationships as Scrooge begins to foster them."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ONE!&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"One! is an event, possibly emphasizing a moment of significance or unity, as indicated by its isolated representation in the text."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e0a61ff58550112a553d6ec01d2c0891</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE LIGHTHOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Lighthouse stands on a solitary reef, providing a sense of guidance and hope amidst the tumultuous sea."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE CHAISE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Chaise is a type of carriage used to transport Scrooge and Little Fan, suggesting warmth in their reunion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE WINDOW&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Window serves as a connection between Scrooge's physical world and the spectral realm of the ghosts and phantoms he encounters."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Window through which Scrooge looks signifies a viewpoint into the external world and reflects his isolation and confusion."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;DOLL'S FRYING PAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Doll's frying pan signifies the innocence and playfulness of childhood, as well as the humorous situations created by the children."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9</data>
    </node>
