    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Christmas is a recurring theme in the text, representing a time of joy and reflection, contrasting with Scrooge's current views."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is contextualized through the mentions of toys and presents, symbolizing joy, family, and the spirit of giving."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a holiday representing joy, generosity, and social connections, which Scrooge vehemently opposes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a seasonal celebration associated with kindness, generosity, and community spirit, contrasted with Scrooge's cynicism."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a theme in the text, representing joy and social gathering, which Scrooge actively dislikes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a time for reflection, joy, and connection among people, as well as a theme central to Scrooge's journey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a time of festivity and generosity, contrasting with Scrooge's attitude toward merriment and social responsibility."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is depicted as a time of joy, generosity, and community, contrasting with Scrooge's character."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is highlighted as a season of goodwill and a time for reflection, underlining the themes of redemption and transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is portrayed as a time of joy and transformation, particularly in the context of Scrooge's change of heart."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the annual holiday celebrated by the Cratchit family, marked by joy, togetherness, and a spirit of generosity despite their financial constraints."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive occasion around which Scrooge's reflections and emotional journey revolve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive occasion during which the story takes place, symbolizing generosity, transformation, and family togetherness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday season that serves as a central theme in the narrative, representing generosity, kindness, and transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday season that the Ghost of Christmas Present embodies, representing themes of joy, generosity, and celebration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas represents a festive occasion during which the scenes described unfold, characterized by joy and celebration despite the severe weather."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas represents a time of family gathering and celebration, with a backdrop of warmth despite the family's struggles."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas symbolizes joy, celebration, and togetherness, contrasting with Scrooge's current perspective on life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas symbolizes joy, redemption, and the spirit of giving that Scrooge ultimately embraces after his transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE PARTING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Parting refers to the emotional moment when the Cratchit family acknowledges their separation from Tiny Tim, emphasizing the theme of loss."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LONDON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"London is the location where the narrative unfolds, representing a bustling city backdrop that contrasts with the themes of poverty and personal transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"London is the setting of the story, representing a bustling city where various events, including festive celebrations, take place."&lt;SEP&gt;"London serves as the setting for the story, showcasing the social disparities and winter hardships faced by its citizens during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S COUNTING-HOUSE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's Counting-House is the workplace of Scrooge, illustrating his obsessive dedication to business and wealth accumulation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DUALITY OF EXISTENCE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Duality of Existence represents the contrast between Scrooge's current life and the potential for a more fulfilled life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE ECHO OF KINDNESS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Echo of Kindness signifies the lingering impressions of compassion that Scrooge begins to acknowledge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MOSAIC OF HUMANITY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Mosaic of Humanity represents the diverse relationships and connections that define a fulfilled life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE BOY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Boy is a character who engages with Scrooge, showing curiosity and excitement while assisting him in his plans for Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Boy is a younger version of Scrooge, representing innocence and the potential for happiness that Scrooge once had."&lt;SEP&gt;"The boy, who is unnamed, represents the manifestation of societal neglect, embodying the consequences of ignorance and poverty."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE HAPPY SCENE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
