      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GAOL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Gaol refers to a place of confinement for those accused of crimes, representing societal neglect and the consequences of poverty."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DEAD MAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Dead Man is referenced throughout the dialogue, representing a life characterized by avarice and isolation, ultimately leading to his death and the subsequent actions of others."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPECTER OF MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Specter of Marley serves as a reminder of the need for transformation and moral reckoning for Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE MARVEL OF TRANSFORMATION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Marvel of Transformation encapsulates the wonder Scrooge feels as he makes significant changes in his life."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE JOURNEY OF INTROSPECTION&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Journey of Introspection encompasses Scrooge’s path as he confronts himself and prepares for change."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
