    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">SCROOGE is a central character known for his miserly and cold-hearted nature, often displaying disdain for Christmas and a lack of empathy towards others. Throughout the narrative, he grapples with his past, reflecting on his life experiences, his solitary lifestyle, and his previous actions that have defined him as a stingy individual. His initial skepticism toward supernatural encounters, particularly with Marley’s Ghost, is challenged as he meets various spiritual entities—namely, the Ghost of Christmas Past, the Ghost of Christmas Present, and the Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come.

As SCROOGE progresses through these transformative encounters, he reflects on themes of redemption, change, and the implications of his life choices. His journey includes moments of sorrow as he recalls his lonely childhood during Christmas and observes the morbid actions of others, which highlight his own failures in compassion. He expresses concern for the poor, particularly for the future of Tiny Tim, which showcases the shift in his attitudes as he begins to recognize the importance of generosity and kindness.

Ultimately, SCROOGE undergoes a dramatic transformation—moving from a miserly figure entrenched in greed and indifference to someone who embraces joy, goodwill, and charitable actions towards others, particularly his employee Bob Cratchit. His experiences culminate in a moral awakening, allowing him to celebrate Christmas with newfound joy and compassion, thus embodying the true spirit of the holiday and securing his redemption.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550</data>
