    <edge source="&quot;THE GHOST&quot;" target="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">48.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is confronted by The Ghost, which compels him to reflect on his past and the choices that led to his current misery."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge is questioning the Ghost about its existence and purpose, indicating a struggle with belief and skepticism."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost acts as a catalyst for Scrooge's self-reflection and reconnection with his past."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost acts as a guide for Scrooge, revealing the emotional implications of death and urging him towards a transformation of character."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost interacts with Scrooge to help him reflect on his past and understand the significance of Christmas."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost interacts with Scrooge, providing him with insights about the consequences of his actions and the importance of caring for others, particularly for those like Tiny Tim."</data>
